tldr: The user wanted to add a database and admin dashboard to their sleep
  questionnaire application. I created a plan, implemented the database, API
  routes, and an admin dashboard with authentication, then simplified the
  authentication using Next.js middleware. All features were tested and
  confirmed working.
overview: The user's intent was to enhance their sleep questionnaire application
  by adding a database to store responses and an admin dashboard for data access
  and management. The approach involved updating the application's data model to
  include new demographic fields, implementing a PostgreSQL database (NeonDB)
  via Prisma, and developing a set of API endpoints for data submission,
  retrieval, and CSV export. A key decision was to use a simple password-based
  authentication system, which was initially implemented with custom session
  management but later refined to leverage Next.js middleware for more
  streamlined route protection. The outcome is a fully functional system where
  questionnaire responses are securely stored, accessible through a protected
  admin dashboard, and exportable as CSV, meeting all the specified
  requirements. All features were thoroughly tested and confirmed to be working
  as expected.
